{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1753,"text":"Cancer."},{"time":3301,"text":"Many of us have lost family,\nfriends or loved ones"},{"time":6390,"text":"to this horrible disease."},{"time":8094,"text":"I know there are some of you\nin the audience"},{"time":10214,"text":"who are cancer survivors,"},{"time":11479,"text":"or who are fighting cancer at this moment."},{"time":13658,"text":"My heart goes out to you."},{"time":15673,"text":"While this word often conjures up\nemotions of sadness and anger and fear,"},{"time":20971,"text":"I bring you good news\nfrom the front lines of cancer research."},{"time":24509,"text":"The fact is, we are starting to win\nthe war on cancer."},{"time":29318,"text":"In fact, we lie at the intersection"},{"time":31045,"text":"of the three of the most exciting\ndevelopments within cancer research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35258,"text":"The first is cancer genomics."},{"time":37567,"text":"The genome is a composition"},{"time":39616,"text":"of all the genetic information\nencoded by DNA"},{"time":42576,"text":"in an organism."},{"time":43967,"text":"In cancers, changes\nin the DNA called mutations"},{"time":46832,"text":"are what drive these cancers\nto go out of control."},{"time":50070,"text":"Around 10 years ago,\nI was part of the team at Johns Hopkins"},{"time":53386,"text":"that first mapped\nthe mutations of cancers."},{"time":56008,"text":"We did this first for colorectal,"},{"time":58218,"text":"breast, pancreatic and brain cancers."},{"time":61164,"text":"And since then, there have been\nover 90 projects in 70 countries"},{"time":64700,"text":"all over the world,"},{"time":66314,"text":"working to understand\nthe genetic basis of these diseases."},{"time":69713,"text":"Today, tens of thousands\nof cancers are understood"},{"time":72791,"text":"down to exquisite molecular detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76200,"text":"The second revolution\nis precision medicine,"},{"time":78526,"text":"also known as \"personalized medicine.\""},{"time":80954,"text":"Instead of one-size-fits-all methods\nto be able to treat cancers,"},{"time":84555,"text":"there is a whole new class of drugs\nthat are able to target cancers"},{"time":88234,"text":"based on their unique genetic profile."},{"time":90917,"text":"Today, there are a host\nof these tailor-made drugs,"},{"time":93871,"text":"called targeted therapies,"},{"time":95225,"text":"available to physicians even today"},{"time":97432,"text":"to be able to personalize\ntheir therapy for their patients,"},{"time":100719,"text":"and many others are in development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103296,"text":"The third exciting revolution\nis immunotherapy,"},{"time":106618,"text":"and this is really exciting."},{"time":109045,"text":"Scientists have been able\nto leverage the immune system"},{"time":111779,"text":"in the fight against cancer."},{"time":113832,"text":"For example, there have been ways\nwhere we find the off switches of cancer,"},{"time":118052,"text":"and new drugs have been able\nto turn the immune system back on,"},{"time":121520,"text":"to be able to fight cancer."},{"time":123132,"text":"In addition, there are ways\nwhere you can take away immune cells"},{"time":127247,"text":"from the body,"},{"time":128431,"text":"train them, engineer them\nand put them back into the body"},{"time":131542,"text":"to fight cancer."},{"time":132943,"text":"Almost sounds like\nscience fiction, doesn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136090,"text":"While I was a researcher\nat the National Cancer Institute,"},{"time":139130,"text":"I had the privilege of working\nwith some of the pioneers of this field"},{"time":142609,"text":"and watched the development firsthand."},{"time":144879,"text":"It's been pretty amazing."},{"time":146346,"text":"Today, over 600 clinical trials are open,"},{"time":149375,"text":"actively recruiting patients\nto explore all aspects in immunotherapy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154664,"text":"While these three exciting\nrevolutions are ongoing,"},{"time":157749,"text":"unfortunately, this is only the beginning,"},{"time":159797,"text":"and there are still many, many challenges."},{"time":163032,"text":"Let me illustrate with a patient."},{"time":166201,"text":"Here is a patient\nwith a skin cancer called melanoma."},{"time":169136,"text":"It's horrible; the cancer\nhas gone everywhere."},{"time":173206,"text":"However, scientists were able\nto map the mutations of this cancer"},{"time":176950,"text":"and give a specific treatment\nthat targets one of the mutations."},{"time":181950,"text":"And the result is almost miraculous."},{"time":184427,"text":"Tumors almost seem to melt away."},{"time":187910,"text":"Unfortunately, this is not\nthe end of the story."},{"time":191077,"text":"A few months later, this picture is taken."},{"time":194157,"text":"The tumor has come back."},{"time":196627,"text":"The question is: Why?"},{"time":198892,"text":"The answer is tumor heterogeneity."},{"time":202107,"text":"Let me explain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205124,"text":"Even a cancer as small\nas one centimeter in diameter"},{"time":208636,"text":"harbors over a hundred million\ndifferent cells."},{"time":211848,"text":"While genetically similar,"},{"time":213753,"text":"there are small differences\nin these different cancers"},{"time":216486,"text":"that make them differently prone\nto different drugs."},{"time":219367,"text":"So even if you have a drug\nthat's highly effective,"},{"time":221819,"text":"that kills almost all the cells,"},{"time":223578,"text":"there is a chance\nthat there's a small population"},{"time":226792,"text":"that's resistant to the drug."},{"time":228590,"text":"This ultimately is the population"},{"time":230636,"text":"that comes back,"},{"time":231824,"text":"and takes over the patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233887,"text":"So then the question is:\nWhat do we do with this information?"},{"time":236770,"text":"Well, the key, then,"},{"time":238056,"text":"is to apply all these exciting\nadvancements in cancer therapy earlier,"},{"time":242950,"text":"as soon as we can,"},{"time":244196,"text":"before these resistance clones emerge."},{"time":247230,"text":"The key to cancer and curing cancer\nis early detection."},{"time":252439,"text":"And we intuitively know this."},{"time":254132,"text":"Finding cancer early\nresults in better outcomes,"},{"time":257242,"text":"and the numbers show this as well."},{"time":259312,"text":"For example, in ovarian cancer,\nif you detect cancer in stage four,"},{"time":263579,"text":"only 17 percent of the women\nsurvive at five years."},{"time":267268,"text":"However, if you are able to detect\nthis cancer as early as stage one,"},{"time":271720,"text":"over 92 percent of women will survive."},{"time":274925,"text":"But the sad fact is, only 15 percent\nof women are detected at stage one,"},{"time":279752,"text":"whereas the vast majority, 70 percent,\nare detected in stages three and four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285348,"text":"We desperately need\nbetter detection mechanisms for cancers."},{"time":290053,"text":"The current best ways to screen cancer\nfall into one of three categories."},{"time":294355,"text":"First is medical procedures,"},{"time":296554,"text":"which is like colonoscopy\nfor colon cancer."},{"time":299486,"text":"Second is protein biomarkers,\nlike PSA for prostate cancer."},{"time":304126,"text":"Or third, imaging techniques,"},{"time":307062,"text":"such as mammography for breast cancer."},{"time":310419,"text":"Medical procedures are the gold standard;"},{"time":312869,"text":"however, they are highly invasive"},{"time":314989,"text":"and require a large\ninfrastructure to implement."},{"time":318682,"text":"Protein markers, while effective\nin some populations,"},{"time":321910,"text":"are not very specific\nin some circumstances,"},{"time":324423,"text":"resulting in high numbers\nof false positives,"},{"time":327030,"text":"which then results in unnecessary work-ups\nand unnecessary procedures."},{"time":333322,"text":"Imaging methods,\nwhile useful in some populations,"},{"time":336961,"text":"expose patients to harmful radiation."},{"time":339882,"text":"In addition, it is not applicable\nto all patients."},{"time":342520,"text":"For example, mammography has problems\nin women with dense breasts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347036,"text":"So what we need is a method\nthat is noninvasive,"},{"time":350454,"text":"that is light in infrastructure,"},{"time":352245,"text":"that is highly specific,"},{"time":354148,"text":"that also does not have false positives,"},{"time":357393,"text":"does not use any radiation"},{"time":359383,"text":"and is applicable to large populations."},{"time":362338,"text":"Even more importantly,"},{"time":363536,"text":"we need a method\nto be able to detect cancers"},{"time":365756,"text":"before they're 100 million cells in size."},{"time":369060,"text":"Does such a technology exist?"},{"time":371008,"text":"Well, I wouldn't be up here\ngiving a talk if it didn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374902,"text":"I'm excited to tell you about\nthis latest technology we've developed."},{"time":379215,"text":"Central to our technology\nis a simple blood test."},{"time":382382,"text":"The blood circulatory system,\nwhile seemingly mundane,"},{"time":386136,"text":"is essential for you to survive,"},{"time":388490,"text":"providing oxygen\nand nutrients to your cells,"},{"time":391019,"text":"and removing waste and carbon dioxide."},{"time":393648,"text":"Here's a key biological insight:"},{"time":396420,"text":"Cancer cells grow and die\nfaster than normal cells,"},{"time":399527,"text":"and when they die,"},{"time":400747,"text":"DNA is shed into the blood system."},{"time":403492,"text":"Since we know the signatures\nof these cancer cells"},{"time":406286,"text":"from all the different cancer\ngenome sequencing projects,"},{"time":409014,"text":"we can look for those signals in the blood"},{"time":411079,"text":"to be able to detect these cancers early."},{"time":414409,"text":"So instead of waiting for cancers\nto be large enough to cause symptoms,"},{"time":418232,"text":"or for them to be dense enough\nto show up on imaging,"},{"time":421155,"text":"or for them to be prominent enough"},{"time":423621,"text":"for you to be able to visualize\non medical procedures,"},{"time":426885,"text":"we can start looking for cancers\nwhile they are relatively pretty small,"},{"time":430901,"text":"by looking for these small amounts\nof DNA in the blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435815,"text":"So let me tell you how we do this."},{"time":437514,"text":"First, like I said, we start off\nwith a simple blood test --"},{"time":440402,"text":"no radiation, no complicated equipment --"},{"time":443001,"text":"a simple blood test."},{"time":444491,"text":"Then the blood is shipped to us,"},{"time":446051,"text":"and what we do\nis extract the DNA out of it."},{"time":449110,"text":"While your body is mostly healthy cells,"},{"time":451530,"text":"most of the DNA that's detected\nwill be from healthy cells."},{"time":455834,"text":"However, there will be a small amount,\nless than one percent,"},{"time":458925,"text":"that comes from the cancer cells."},{"time":461545,"text":"Then we use molecular biology methods\nto be able to enrich this DNA"},{"time":465775,"text":"for areas of the genome which are known\nto be associated with cancer,"},{"time":470211,"text":"based on the information\nfrom the cancer genomics projects."},{"time":473664,"text":"We're able to then put this DNA\ninto DNA-sequencing machines"},{"time":477565,"text":"and are able to digitize the DNA\ninto A's, C's, T's and G's"},{"time":482279,"text":"and have this final readout."},{"time":484451,"text":"Ultimately, we have information\nof billions of letters"},{"time":490465,"text":"that output from this run."},{"time":494635,"text":"We then apply statistical\nand computational methods"},{"time":497879,"text":"to be able to find\nthe small signal that's present,"},{"time":500575,"text":"indicative of the small amount\nof cancer DNA in the blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505278,"text":"So does this actually work in patients?"},{"time":507727,"text":"Well, because there's no way\nof really predicting right now"},{"time":511241,"text":"which patients will get cancer,"},{"time":512773,"text":"we use the next best population:"},{"time":515441,"text":"cancers in remission;"},{"time":517552,"text":"specifically, lung cancer."},{"time":520405,"text":"The sad fact is, even with the best drugs\nthat we have today,"},{"time":523738,"text":"most lung cancers come back."},{"time":525974,"text":"The key, then, is to see"},{"time":527298,"text":"whether we're able to detect\nthese recurrences of cancers"},{"time":530973,"text":"earlier than with standard methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533339,"text":"We just finished a major trial"},{"time":535740,"text":"with Professor Charles Swanton\nat University College London,"},{"time":539511,"text":"examining this."},{"time":540701,"text":"Let me walk you through\nan example of one patient."},{"time":544766,"text":"Here's an example of one patient\nwho undergoes surgery"},{"time":547617,"text":"at time point zero,"},{"time":548809,"text":"and then undergoes chemotherapy."},{"time":551709,"text":"Then the patient is under remission."},{"time":554218,"text":"He is monitored using clinical exams\nand imaging methods."},{"time":559149,"text":"Around day 450, unfortunately,\nthe cancer comes back."},{"time":565266,"text":"The question is:\nAre we able to catch this earlier?"},{"time":567775,"text":"During this whole time,\nwe've been collecting blood serially"},{"time":571544,"text":"to be able to measure\nthe amount of ctDNA in the blood."},{"time":575560,"text":"So at the initial time point, as expected,"},{"time":578881,"text":"there's a high level\nof cancer DNA in the blood."},{"time":582603,"text":"However, this goes away to zero\nin subsequent time points"},{"time":586294,"text":"and remains negligible\nafter subsequent points."},{"time":590993,"text":"However, around day 340, we see the rise\nof cancer DNA in the blood,"},{"time":596290,"text":"and eventually, it goes up higher\nfor days 400 and 450."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601415,"text":"Here's the key, if you've missed it:"},{"time":603871,"text":"At day 340, we see the rise\nin the cancer DNA in the blood."},{"time":608876,"text":"That means we are catching this cancer\nover a hundred days earlier"},{"time":613116,"text":"than traditional methods."},{"time":615101,"text":"This is a hundred days earlier\nwhere we can give therapies,"},{"time":617938,"text":"a hundred days earlier\nwhere we can do surgical interventions,"},{"time":621281,"text":"or even a hundred days less\nfor the cancer to grow"},{"time":624338,"text":"or a hundred days less\nfor resistance to occur."},{"time":628682,"text":"For some patients, this hundred days\nmeans the matter of life and death."},{"time":633417,"text":"We're really excited\nabout this information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636539,"text":"Because of this assignment,\nwe've done additional studies now"},{"time":639660,"text":"in other cancers,"},{"time":640946,"text":"including breast cancer, lung cancer"},{"time":644305,"text":"and ovarian cancer,"},{"time":646068,"text":"and I can't wait to see how much earlier\nwe can find these cancers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652354,"text":"Ultimately, I have a dream,"},{"time":654394,"text":"a dream of two vials of blood,"},{"time":657536,"text":"and that, in the future, as part of all\nof our standard physical exams,"},{"time":661425,"text":"we'll have two vials of blood drawn."},{"time":663821,"text":"And from these two vials of blood\nwe will be able to compare"},{"time":667187,"text":"the DNA from all known\nsignatures of cancer,"},{"time":670722,"text":"and hopefully then detect cancers\nmonths to even years earlier."},{"time":675359,"text":"Even with the therapies we have currently,"},{"time":677554,"text":"this could mean that millions\nof lives could be saved."},{"time":680179,"text":"And if you add on to that\nrecent advancements in immunotherapy"},{"time":684374,"text":"and targeted therapies,"},{"time":685690,"text":"the end of cancer is in sight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688934,"text":"The next time you hear the word \"cancer,\""},{"time":691115,"text":"I want you to add to the emotions: hope."},{"time":694303,"text":"Hold on."},{"time":696342,"text":"Cancer researchers all around the world\nare working feverishly"},{"time":699939,"text":"to beat this disease,"},{"time":701119,"text":"and tremendous progress is being made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703956,"text":"This is the beginning of the end."},{"time":706380,"text":"We will win the war on cancer."},{"time":708861,"text":"And to me, this is amazing news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711193,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712384,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}